  82:8:6:"The sixth word of verse (82:8) is divided into 2 morphological segments. A verb and object pronoun. The form II perfect verb (<span class=\"at\">فعل ماض</span>) is third person masculine singular. The verb's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">rā kāf bā</i> (<span class=\"at\">ر ك ب</span>). The attached object pronoun is second person masculine singular."
